Heywood- <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ECMAScript#Fourth_edition">ECMAScript 4.0,</a> which you'll know as Javascript 2.0 is being worked on actively.  It's an <a href="http://www.ecma-international.org/publications/standards/Stnindex.htm">open standard specification</a> so you're welcome to jump in and help bring it to market faster if you're feeling the limitations of the current spec.<br><span class="smallcopy">posted by <a href="http://www.metafilter.com/user/3625" target="_self">gen</a> at <a href="/61049/Douglas-Crockford-Teaches-JavaScript#1687609" target="_self">10:44 PM</a>  on May 10, 2007 </span></div><br><br> 
