<a name="1687624"></a><div class="comments">Heywood Mogroot: <em>Surprisingly, there's no server-side lock-in with Silverlight. </em><br />
<br />
Not surprisingly, that's because <a href="http://news.netcraft.com/archives/web_server_survey.html">Apache has over 50%</a> of the market (primarily on *nix platforms.)  Microsoft is FORCED to support non MSFT solutions on the server.  It's not a friendly gesture, is a strategy, a tactic.  Redmond doesn't support other platforms except when they are forced to by the marketplace.<br><span class="smallcopy">posted by <a href="http://www.metafilter.com/user/3625" target="_self">gen</a> at <a href="/61049/Douglas-Crockford-Teaches-JavaScript#1687624" target="_self">11:04 PM</a>  on May 10, 2007 </span></div><br><br> 
